  - 146
By: Sri Ramakrishna
---
Can you ever see God if you do not direct your whole mind toward Him?
The Bhâgavata speaks about Sukadeva. When he walked about he looked
like a soldier with fixed bayonet. His gaze did not wander： it had
only one goal and that was God. This is the meaning of yoga.
